1
00:00:43,043 --> 00:00:45,713
CHAPTER 4:
STARS ARE BORN OUT OF CHAOS

2
00:00:45,796 --> 00:00:47,256
-Jeon Ji-min.
-Here!

3
00:00:48,758 --> 00:00:50,217
-Oh Ji-ho.
-Here!

4
00:00:50,801 --> 00:00:51,761
-Kim Ga-yeong.
-Here!

5
00:00:51,844 --> 00:00:54,680
He's taking attendance
before introducing himself?

6
00:00:54,764 --> 00:00:56,056
Who does he think he is?

7
00:00:56,140 --> 00:00:56,974
Kim Dan-ji.

8
00:00:58,184 --> 00:00:59,393
Here!

9
00:00:59,477 --> 00:01:01,061
-Kim Yeong-jae.
-Here!

10
00:01:02,021 --> 00:01:03,355
-Eun Ha-su.
-Here.

11
00:01:07,067 --> 00:01:08,903
I hear you won gold at the KMO?

12
00:01:10,279 --> 00:01:11,155
Yes.

13
00:01:11,238 --> 00:01:12,198
KMO?

14
00:01:12,823 --> 00:01:14,033
What's that?

15
00:01:14,116 --> 00:01:14,950
No idea.

16
00:01:15,034 --> 00:01:16,285
How was it?

17
00:01:18,287 --> 00:01:19,371
Not that difficult.

18
00:01:19,955 --> 00:01:22,666
Why is he talking to her
and only calling others' names?

19
00:01:23,417 --> 00:01:25,127
Are they best friends or something?

20
00:01:26,670 --> 00:01:27,797
-Oh A-rin.
-Here.

21
00:01:28,798 --> 00:01:30,132
-Choi Yu-mi.
-Here.

22
00:01:31,258 --> 00:01:32,468
-Yeo Eui-ju.
-Here.

23
00:01:39,099 --> 00:01:40,518
-Yeo Eui-ju?
-Here.

24
00:01:42,436 --> 00:01:44,063
-Yeo Eui-ju!
-Here!

25
00:01:49,860 --> 00:01:51,570
-Choi Go-ya.
-Here.

26
00:01:52,071 --> 00:01:52,947
Choi Ji-a.

27
00:01:58,160 --> 00:01:59,578
Choi Ji-a?

28
00:01:59,662 --> 00:02:00,496
Here.

29
00:02:08,712 --> 00:02:11,841
I am Mr. Ga, your new homeroom teacher.

30
00:02:11,924 --> 00:02:13,634
-So handsome!
-So handsome!

31
00:02:22,476 --> 00:02:24,645
Math is a discipline
that knows no falsehood.

32
00:02:25,354 --> 00:02:27,273
Euclid's Elements begins like this.

33
00:02:27,356 --> 00:02:29,650
"A point is that which has no part."

34
00:02:30,693 --> 00:02:31,777
Isn't that beautiful?

35
00:02:34,530 --> 00:02:35,823
Points connect to form lines.

36
00:02:35,906 --> 00:02:37,408
Lines move to create planes.

37
00:02:37,491 --> 00:02:39,702
Planes form boundaries that make solids.

38
00:02:39,785 --> 00:02:40,619
And solids

39
00:02:40,703 --> 00:02:42,538
exist within time and space.

40
00:02:42,621 --> 00:02:43,539
In other words,

41
00:02:44,373 --> 00:02:47,001
math is the language that explains
how the universe exists.

42
00:02:47,626 --> 00:02:49,712
That's why to understand mathematics

43
00:02:49,795 --> 00:02:52,172
is to understand the universe
you were born into.

44
00:02:57,845 --> 00:03:00,222
I think of you as stars in that universe.

45
00:03:00,848 --> 00:03:03,183
Each of you shining,
each with your own world.

46
00:03:05,102 --> 00:03:06,437
When a star is born,

47
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:08,480
countless clouds of dust
surround it so densely

48
00:03:08,564 --> 00:03:10,065
you can't even see an inch ahead.

49
00:03:10,149 --> 00:03:11,275
That's why people say

50
00:03:12,359 --> 00:03:14,361
stars are born out of chaos.

51
00:03:17,239 --> 00:03:18,449
You're probably the same.

52
00:03:18,532 --> 00:03:20,618
-Oh, that's so deep.
-How cool is that?

53
00:03:20,701 --> 00:03:21,619
In the midst of that chaos,

54
00:03:21,702 --> 00:03:24,330
some of you may have figured out
what you like, what you don't,

55
00:03:24,997 --> 00:03:27,416
what you're good at
and what you want to do.

56
00:03:27,499 --> 00:03:28,834
But for those that haven't,

57
00:03:29,752 --> 00:03:31,045
I hope the rest of this semester

58
00:03:31,128 --> 00:03:33,130
will be the time you find it.

59
00:03:36,467 --> 00:03:38,177
If you're having difficulty,
I'll help you.

60
00:03:41,263 --> 00:03:42,723
But it must be you yourself

61
00:03:43,349 --> 00:03:45,351
that takes that final step.

62
00:03:47,937 --> 00:03:49,772
What the heck?

63
00:03:49,855 --> 00:03:52,691
All that guff about stars
and the universe to say that?

64
00:03:52,775 --> 00:03:54,151
His pride in math is unbelievable.

65
00:03:54,234 --> 00:03:55,653
What a nerdy math geek.

66
00:03:57,154 --> 00:03:58,113
Yeo Eui-ju.

67
00:03:59,365 --> 00:04:00,491
Yes, sir.

68
00:04:00,574 --> 00:04:02,993
What score did you get in math
in the last mock exam?

69
00:04:03,786 --> 00:04:05,871
Why is he asking that out of the blue?

70
00:04:07,081 --> 00:04:08,248
It was…

71
00:04:08,832 --> 00:04:10,000
I can't hear you.

72
00:04:11,543 --> 00:04:12,795
Four…

73
00:04:12,878 --> 00:04:13,712
Forty…

74
00:04:16,006 --> 00:04:17,216
Four points, sir.

75
00:04:24,056 --> 00:04:25,182
Four points?

76
00:04:28,143 --> 00:04:29,103
If that's all you got…

77
00:04:35,025 --> 00:04:37,403
you ought to go back to grade school.

78
00:04:45,452 --> 00:04:46,704
Come with me to the teachers' office.

79
00:04:48,038 --> 00:04:48,872
Class dismissed.

80
00:04:49,915 --> 00:04:51,583
Why me?

81
00:04:55,963 --> 00:04:58,424
EPISODE 2

82
00:05:17,985 --> 00:05:18,819
Sir.

83
00:05:20,529 --> 00:05:24,199
I really didn't film you.

84
00:05:24,908 --> 00:05:25,743
PHOTO GALLERY

85
00:05:25,826 --> 00:05:26,744
See for yourself.

86
00:05:26,827 --> 00:05:28,996
This is my video folder.

87
00:05:29,079 --> 00:05:31,415
And this is my recently deleted folder.

88
00:05:31,498 --> 00:05:32,833
See, it's empty.

89
00:05:34,501 --> 00:05:35,335
See?

90
00:05:40,299 --> 00:05:41,759
Is that not why I'm here?

91
00:05:43,719 --> 00:05:47,347
Is it because
I came into the homeroom after you?

92
00:05:50,225 --> 00:05:51,393
Then…

93
00:05:51,477 --> 00:05:52,728
His pride in math is unbelievable.

94
00:05:52,811 --> 00:05:54,063
What a nerdy math geek.

95
00:05:55,814 --> 00:05:58,692
If you perhaps heard what I said earlier

96
00:05:58,776 --> 00:06:01,820
I was just upset about my phone, and…

97
00:06:06,950 --> 00:06:08,869
I'm sorry, sir.
I must have been out of my mind.

98
00:06:08,952 --> 00:06:10,746
-How could I have done that?
-Enough.

99
00:06:11,497 --> 00:06:13,248
How could you only get four points?

100
00:06:23,509 --> 00:06:26,470
I don't even want to open my math book.

101
00:06:27,262 --> 00:06:30,015
It's difficult and no fun.
I don't even get the point of studying it.

102
00:06:30,599 --> 00:06:31,767
I just hate it.

103
00:06:32,935 --> 00:06:33,769
Difficult?

104
00:06:34,478 --> 00:06:35,437
No fun?

105
00:06:36,355 --> 00:06:37,189
You just hate it?

106
00:06:37,773 --> 00:06:38,607
Yes.

107
00:06:41,610 --> 00:06:42,569
What is math?

108
00:06:44,238 --> 00:06:45,906
Math is

109
00:06:47,157 --> 00:06:48,158
math.

110
00:06:48,826 --> 00:06:52,037
How can you be so sure you hate math
when you don't even know what it is?

111
00:06:52,496 --> 00:06:55,290
Math is where philosophy has blossomed.
And what is philosophy?

112
00:06:56,291 --> 00:06:57,918
It's thinking precisely.

113
00:06:58,877 --> 00:06:59,837
Thinking!

114
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:02,131
Why do mathematicians prove things
through logic?

115
00:07:02,214 --> 00:07:03,799
Why are numbers the root of everything?

116
00:07:03,882 --> 00:07:05,217
Have you considered such things?

117
00:07:05,884 --> 00:07:08,137
-No.
-Exactly. So how can you say you hate it?

118
00:07:11,890 --> 00:07:13,684
So, to reflect on your ignorance of math

119
00:07:13,767 --> 00:07:16,395
and reconsider its origins,

120
00:07:17,771 --> 00:07:19,690
I want you to write a letter to Euclid.

121
00:07:19,773 --> 00:07:21,608
Twenty pages. By the final bell tomorrow.

122
00:07:22,484 --> 00:07:23,360
Twenty pages?

123
00:07:23,443 --> 00:07:24,695
Go. And send Choi Ji-a in.

124
00:07:25,821 --> 00:07:26,947
But, sir!

125
00:07:31,201 --> 00:07:32,035
Yes, sir.

126
00:07:46,091 --> 00:07:47,426
Thank you.

127
00:07:48,218 --> 00:07:49,428
What's your next class?

128
00:07:53,557 --> 00:07:55,309
-Hello.
-Good morning.

129
00:07:58,187 --> 00:08:01,481
I'm sorry about Mr. Ga
having a go at you earlier.

130
00:08:02,316 --> 00:08:04,526
He can be a bit prickly at times.

131
00:08:05,444 --> 00:08:07,696
Sometimes he can be childish and immature,

132
00:08:08,322 --> 00:08:09,990
but he's not a bad guy at heart.

133
00:08:11,658 --> 00:08:12,492
I see.

134
00:08:12,576 --> 00:08:13,994
Sir, that's not the issue here.

135
00:08:14,077 --> 00:08:17,789
You're being gaslit right now.

136
00:08:17,873 --> 00:08:19,875
There's no need to defend him like that.

137
00:08:19,958 --> 00:08:21,501
This is me.

138
00:08:22,961 --> 00:08:24,254
It was nice to meet you.

139
00:08:31,678 --> 00:08:33,096
He's such an angel.

140
00:08:34,890 --> 00:08:37,434
Why does an angel like that
hang out with a demon like him?

141
00:08:44,900 --> 00:08:45,776
Ji-a.

142
00:08:48,779 --> 00:08:49,905
Choi Ji-a!

143
00:08:51,031 --> 00:08:52,157
Hey, wake up.

144
00:08:53,075 --> 00:08:55,827
I said wake up.

145
00:08:59,206 --> 00:09:00,249
Mr. Ga wants to see you.

146
00:09:09,508 --> 00:09:10,801
What did he say?

147
00:09:12,803 --> 00:09:14,429
He wants me to write an essay.

148
00:09:14,513 --> 00:09:15,806
Twenty pages at that.

149
00:09:15,889 --> 00:09:17,307
Because you mocked him?

150
00:09:17,391 --> 00:09:18,308
No.

151
00:09:18,934 --> 00:09:20,644
Because I got four points in math.

152
00:09:26,483 --> 00:09:27,526
Why were you late?

153
00:09:28,026 --> 00:09:30,946
Even if you overslept or didn't want
to come, there must be a reason.

154
00:09:35,075 --> 00:09:37,786
Coming to school on time
is also a kind of promise.

155
00:09:43,208 --> 00:09:44,626
Be on time from now on.

156
00:09:44,710 --> 00:09:46,962
And if you can't, please explain why.

157
00:09:47,546 --> 00:09:49,339
-Yes, sir.
-Off you go.

158
00:09:57,264 --> 00:09:59,516
Oh, you've been lumbered with her, I see.

159
00:10:00,309 --> 00:10:04,730
With kids from the shelter, just be
grateful if they don't cause any trouble.

160
00:10:04,813 --> 00:10:08,400
Don't wear yourself out
trying to establish your authority.

161
00:10:08,483 --> 00:10:10,444
Just get through the year
without incident.

162
00:10:10,527 --> 00:10:11,611
That's your best bet.

163
00:10:16,033 --> 00:10:18,368
CHAPTER 5:
YOU'RE SOFT AND SQUISHY

164
00:10:18,452 --> 00:10:20,996
"Our hall, is a hall of love,
touched by old customs."

165
00:10:21,079 --> 00:10:24,875
"Sun, lower your crystal eyes,
which are like those of a gentle doe."

166
00:10:24,958 --> 00:10:27,919
"And I will smooth my hair,
which is tangled like a lion's mane."

167
00:10:28,712 --> 00:10:31,006
From now on, when I'm with Dong-ju,

168
00:10:31,089 --> 00:10:33,091
the girl we loved back in the day

169
00:10:33,175 --> 00:10:34,593
will be me.

170
00:10:34,676 --> 00:10:36,261
"…before the bright flame…"

171
00:10:45,604 --> 00:10:47,022
Get your hands down sooner, okay?

172
00:10:47,105 --> 00:10:48,357
Eui-ju!

173
00:10:48,940 --> 00:10:49,816
You got this!

174
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:51,318
Sorry.

175
00:10:57,074 --> 00:10:57,991
Give her a hand!

176
00:10:58,075 --> 00:10:59,701
"Pleased to meet you."

177
00:11:00,577 --> 00:11:01,870
-All right.
-Mr. Noh!

178
00:11:02,371 --> 00:11:03,830
You look like Luciel of Else.

179
00:11:03,914 --> 00:11:06,249
-Right!
-No way!

180
00:11:07,918 --> 00:11:09,920
I was actually scouted
on the street back in college.

181
00:11:10,003 --> 00:11:11,088
-Really?
-Tell us more!

182
00:11:11,171 --> 00:11:12,130
Didn't I tell you this?

183
00:11:13,673 --> 00:11:16,802
-Please tell us!
-Please tell us!

184
00:11:17,386 --> 00:11:18,428
So what happened was…

185
00:11:22,015 --> 00:11:22,974
It comes out like this.

186
00:11:23,058 --> 00:11:25,185
As I said, x minus y isn't zero.

187
00:11:25,268 --> 00:11:27,104
And y minus z isn't zero either.

188
00:11:27,938 --> 00:11:28,772
Try and solve it.

189
00:11:35,612 --> 00:11:37,197
What a jerk!

190
00:11:37,280 --> 00:11:39,366
…the greatest value of x…

191
00:11:47,207 --> 00:11:48,417
Great work today, guys.

192
00:11:49,042 --> 00:11:50,794
-Thank you, sir.
-Thank you, sir.

193
00:11:51,837 --> 00:11:53,004
Where's Choi Ji-a?

194
00:11:59,970 --> 00:12:03,265
She skips homeroom
and leaves straight after class.

195
00:12:07,060 --> 00:12:08,979
Yeo Eui-ju and the next two will clean up.

196
00:12:09,563 --> 00:12:10,480
Why?

197
00:12:10,564 --> 00:12:12,357
-The rotation should start from one.
-Dismissed.

198
00:12:12,941 --> 00:12:14,776
-Thank you, Mr. Ga.
-Thank you, Mr. Ga.

199
00:12:17,946 --> 00:12:20,157
I should've just kept my mouth shut.

200
00:12:23,285 --> 00:12:25,412
That hurts. Can you be more gentle?

201
00:12:26,037 --> 00:12:27,998
How nervous were you to get this stiff?

202
00:12:35,797 --> 00:12:36,631
Hey!

203
00:12:40,218 --> 00:12:41,761
It was so hard writing on the board.

204
00:12:41,845 --> 00:12:43,221
I suddenly stiffened up.

205
00:12:43,305 --> 00:12:44,514
Oh, boy.

206
00:12:46,349 --> 00:12:47,934
How's your tummy?

207
00:12:48,018 --> 00:12:49,227
Okay.

208
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:51,688
How was your class?

209
00:12:52,272 --> 00:12:53,940
Don't ask. I just want to go home.

210
00:12:54,024 --> 00:12:54,983
That feels great.

211
00:12:56,151 --> 00:12:57,486
That arm is fine.

212
00:12:59,112 --> 00:13:00,280
I'm just touching you.

213
00:13:01,031 --> 00:13:02,616
You're soft and squishy.

214
00:13:04,409 --> 00:13:06,786
"You're soft and squishy"?

215
00:13:07,537 --> 00:13:10,123
Don't you think the female students
are braver than the boys?

216
00:13:10,207 --> 00:13:11,082
Tell me about it.

217
00:13:11,708 --> 00:13:13,001
They were staring so blatantly

218
00:13:13,084 --> 00:13:16,505
I didn't know where to look
and ended up losing my train of thought.

219
00:13:17,756 --> 00:13:18,924
It was so embarrassing.

220
00:13:19,007 --> 00:13:20,675
The mighty Yoon Dong-ju

221
00:13:20,759 --> 00:13:22,719
trembling in front of his students.

222
00:13:22,802 --> 00:13:25,889
-Dude, they'd faint if they found out.
-Let go of me.

223
00:13:27,307 --> 00:13:28,350
Amazing!

224
00:13:29,476 --> 00:13:31,269
Why can't I come up
with dialogue like that?

225
00:13:31,978 --> 00:13:33,480
"You're soft and squishy."

226
00:13:34,314 --> 00:13:36,149
"You're soft and squishy."

227
00:13:39,819 --> 00:13:40,987
Mind your own business.

228
00:13:47,702 --> 00:13:50,455
Why do I feel like such a pervert?

229
00:13:56,461 --> 00:13:57,837
-Hello.
-Hey, you're here.

230
00:13:59,214 --> 00:14:00,048
Are you doing okay?

231
00:14:00,632 --> 00:14:02,634
Sorry for asking to switch
with no warning.

232
00:14:02,717 --> 00:14:03,552
Don't sweat it.

233
00:14:04,469 --> 00:14:06,179
Take this medicine.

234
00:14:06,263 --> 00:14:08,139
My mom gave it to me and it's great.

235
00:14:08,223 --> 00:14:09,474
Thanks so much.

236
00:14:10,308 --> 00:14:11,893
I'll do your shift on Thursday.

237
00:14:11,977 --> 00:14:13,562
It's fine. I can do it then too.

238
00:14:13,645 --> 00:14:15,313
I have something to do.

239
00:14:15,397 --> 00:14:16,773
Okay.

240
00:14:16,856 --> 00:14:17,941
Then I'm off.

241
00:14:18,024 --> 00:14:18,858
Okay.

242
00:14:32,914 --> 00:14:34,708
PAZER WEB NOVEL PORTAL
BEST WEB NOVEL RANKINGS

243
00:14:36,126 --> 00:14:37,294
I'm so envious.

244
00:14:38,169 --> 00:14:39,963
When am I going to see my name here?

245
00:14:40,463 --> 00:14:42,549
I WAKE UP AND FIND MYSELF HIS SECRETARY

246
00:14:42,632 --> 00:14:46,052
"When I opened my eyes,
I had become that guy's secretary."

247
00:14:46,136 --> 00:14:48,388
"Reincarnated as a slave
to an evil family"?

248
00:14:48,471 --> 00:14:50,348
Are regression stories all the rage?

249
00:14:51,349 --> 00:14:53,810
No, I tried something similar
and it was a flop.

250
00:14:54,394 --> 00:14:55,604
Shall I go full on for tears?

251
00:14:55,687 --> 00:14:56,938
Obsession and terminal illness?

252
00:14:57,022 --> 00:14:58,815
College senior and junior?

253
00:14:58,898 --> 00:15:01,610
CEO and secretary?
I've done it all before.

254
00:15:04,404 --> 00:15:05,238
Or…

255
00:15:06,573 --> 00:15:08,074
You're soft and squishy.

256
00:15:10,660 --> 00:15:11,578
Friends?

257
00:15:14,122 --> 00:15:16,207
Childhood friends?

258
00:15:18,543 --> 00:15:19,419
I'm bored.

259
00:15:22,714 --> 00:15:25,884
I'm bored, bored, bored.

260
00:15:26,926 --> 00:15:27,886
Jerk.

261
00:15:29,512 --> 00:15:30,847
Stop it.

262
00:15:30,930 --> 00:15:31,931
Jerk.

263
00:15:32,682 --> 00:15:33,725
The pen's a jerk too.

264
00:15:41,650 --> 00:15:42,942
No, no.

265
00:15:43,902 --> 00:15:45,654
Stop fantasizing about your teachers!

266
00:15:46,613 --> 00:15:47,739
Don't do it.

267
00:15:47,822 --> 00:15:48,698
It's wrong.

268
00:15:48,782 --> 00:15:49,991
I'd like to check this out.

269
00:15:56,665 --> 00:15:57,666
Hold on.

270
00:15:57,749 --> 00:16:01,378
CHAPTER 6:
MY FIRST SNOW… IS A BLIZZARD

271
00:16:15,558 --> 00:16:18,061
Hey, turn that off!

272
00:16:18,895 --> 00:16:20,563
That darn alarm.

273
00:16:20,647 --> 00:16:21,564
Someone wake him up.

274
00:16:22,816 --> 00:16:23,650
Okay.

275
00:16:35,328 --> 00:16:36,371
Hey, Da-ju!

276
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:38,289
-Noh Da-ju!
-Yes?

277
00:16:39,040 --> 00:16:40,333
Wake up.

278
00:16:42,001 --> 00:16:43,420
Eat your toast while it's still hot.

279
00:16:44,587 --> 00:16:45,630
Is it crispy?

280
00:16:45,714 --> 00:16:46,673
Hurry up!

281
00:16:51,177 --> 00:16:53,304
Is that an alarm or a siren?

282
00:16:53,388 --> 00:16:54,514
Turn it down a bit.

283
00:16:54,597 --> 00:16:56,558
You ignore it every morning.

284
00:16:57,934 --> 00:16:59,185
It's not crispy.

285
00:16:59,269 --> 00:17:01,855
You should have toasted it more. Crispier!

286
00:17:01,938 --> 00:17:03,148
Then don't eat it.

287
00:17:03,231 --> 00:17:05,150
What's with the racket every morning?

288
00:17:05,233 --> 00:17:06,693
What's the key to living together?

289
00:17:06,776 --> 00:17:08,820
Don't disturb your roommates.
It's common sense.

290
00:17:10,113 --> 00:17:12,198
I can't even have an alarm
in my own house?

291
00:17:13,324 --> 00:17:14,659
Can I have your attention, please?

292
00:17:14,743 --> 00:17:15,994
You're my tenants.

293
00:17:16,077 --> 00:17:18,079
This kind of attitude is problematic.

294
00:17:20,331 --> 00:17:22,333
You should be more considerate of me.

295
00:17:23,376 --> 00:17:25,712
You've got the biggest room.

296
00:17:25,795 --> 00:17:28,214
Whenever something happens,
it's "tenant this, tenant that."

297
00:17:28,298 --> 00:17:30,008
Isn't that a crappy thing to do?

298
00:17:30,091 --> 00:17:31,301
-I'm off.
-Crappy?

299
00:17:31,384 --> 00:17:32,927
Did you just call me crappy?

300
00:17:33,011 --> 00:17:34,304
Finish your breakfast!

301
00:17:34,387 --> 00:17:36,681
You carpool with me every morning.
Pay for it.

302
00:17:36,765 --> 00:17:40,101
What the heck? Your car's a junk.

303
00:17:40,185 --> 00:17:42,896
-We're leaving in ten so hurry up and eat.
-Pay me 50 million won.

304
00:17:42,979 --> 00:17:45,231
MURIM GIRLS' HIGH SCHOOL

305
00:17:45,315 --> 00:17:48,234
The crags and oceans in this poem,

306
00:17:48,318 --> 00:17:50,737
what do you think they mean?

307
00:17:50,820 --> 00:17:52,530
Literally, they just mean
mountain and sea.

308
00:17:52,614 --> 00:17:53,490
But here…

309
00:17:53,573 --> 00:17:55,784
CHARACTERS
KOREAN LITERATURE

310
00:17:56,451 --> 00:17:57,285
Right.

311
00:17:59,162 --> 00:18:00,914
SONG OF THE GREEN MOUNTAIN

312
00:18:00,997 --> 00:18:03,917
Also, the word night in verse four,
and stone in verse five.

313
00:18:04,542 --> 00:18:07,295
DEPENDENT

314
00:18:07,378 --> 00:18:08,630
Has a dependent personality.

315
00:18:08,713 --> 00:18:11,090
Bit of a pushover. Doe-eyed.

316
00:18:11,174 --> 00:18:13,009
KOREAN LITERATURE
DEPENDENT, PUSHOVER, DOE-EYED

317
00:18:14,719 --> 00:18:17,096
We use these words all the time.

318
00:18:17,180 --> 00:18:20,975
But in this poem,
they all have separate other meanings.

319
00:18:21,059 --> 00:18:23,728
Let's leave it here for today. Well done.

320
00:18:23,812 --> 00:18:25,230
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

321
00:18:25,313 --> 00:18:26,689
Watch and learn.

322
00:18:33,738 --> 00:18:34,948
Mr. Yoon!

323
00:18:36,199 --> 00:18:37,200
Yes?

324
00:18:37,283 --> 00:18:39,619
I got you a chalk holder.

325
00:18:40,203 --> 00:18:44,290
Since we still use blackboards, I thought
you might get chalk on your hands.

326
00:19:00,306 --> 00:19:01,432
Thank you.

327
00:19:10,984 --> 00:19:11,901
Go-ya?

328
00:19:13,778 --> 00:19:14,612
Yes?

329
00:19:15,655 --> 00:19:16,781
Thanks for this.

330
00:19:23,705 --> 00:19:24,706
Hey.

331
00:19:28,042 --> 00:19:30,003
Why? What's wrong?

332
00:19:31,296 --> 00:19:32,130
I think

333
00:19:32,964 --> 00:19:34,883
I'm up against a formidable opponent.

334
00:19:37,010 --> 00:19:38,052
My first snow…

335
00:19:39,804 --> 00:19:40,763
is a blizzard.

336
00:20:09,709 --> 00:20:10,793
Loyal, dependable type.

337
00:20:10,877 --> 00:20:13,004
Beefcake with a bulldozer personality.

338
00:20:14,923 --> 00:20:18,426
Reticent but sweet to his man.
An obsessive top.

339
00:20:20,678 --> 00:20:22,764
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

340
00:20:22,847 --> 00:20:24,140
Good morning.

341
00:20:24,223 --> 00:20:27,060
Today, you'll be doing a long-distance run
for the basic fitness test.

342
00:20:27,810 --> 00:20:28,686
Five laps.

343
00:20:28,770 --> 00:20:29,896
-No way!
-Mr. Jung!

344
00:20:29,979 --> 00:20:31,689
The quicker you run,
the more you can rest.

345
00:20:31,773 --> 00:20:33,274
Line up in rows of twelve.

346
00:20:33,358 --> 00:20:34,692
-No way.
-Sir!

347
00:20:35,902 --> 00:20:37,487
Ready!

348
00:21:00,969 --> 00:21:04,222
CRUSH THE CSAT

349
00:21:12,146 --> 00:21:13,314
I'm just touching you.

350
00:21:15,525 --> 00:21:16,693
You're soft and squishy.

351
00:21:21,990 --> 00:21:23,116
What are you doing?

352
00:21:23,199 --> 00:21:24,534
Put some effort in! You got this!

353
00:21:24,617 --> 00:21:26,285
Faster! Move!

354
00:21:26,369 --> 00:21:27,996
Run! You got this!

355
00:21:28,079 --> 00:21:29,247
Faster!

356
00:21:29,956 --> 00:21:30,999
Come on! Faster!

357
00:21:36,462 --> 00:21:37,338
Faster!

358
00:21:38,297 --> 00:21:39,382
Harder!

359
00:21:39,465 --> 00:21:40,800
Faster!

360
00:21:54,647 --> 00:21:55,898
Stop it, Eui-ju!

361
00:21:55,982 --> 00:21:57,191
No!

362
00:21:57,275 --> 00:21:58,568
Stop it!

363
00:22:05,241 --> 00:22:06,075
That's it!

364
00:22:30,600 --> 00:22:32,060
Whoever wins, I don't care!

365
00:22:34,062 --> 00:22:34,937
Are you okay?

366
00:22:40,359 --> 00:22:41,360
I asked if you're okay.

367
00:22:43,905 --> 00:22:45,573
Yes, I'm fine.

368
00:22:48,576 --> 00:22:49,744
Are you a runner?

369
00:22:52,455 --> 00:22:53,331
No.

370
00:22:56,167 --> 00:22:57,585
Want to join after-school sports?

371
00:22:58,461 --> 00:23:01,672
Give it a shot. Wednesdays at five.
We'll focus on the practical exam.

372
00:23:01,756 --> 00:23:03,966
Drop by my office later
for an application form.

373
00:23:07,720 --> 00:23:09,138
You have real talent.

374
00:23:13,601 --> 00:23:16,729
Sir, I'm going to go wash my face.

375
00:23:34,622 --> 00:23:36,833
You're crazy.

376
00:23:36,916 --> 00:23:38,459
Why is my heart beating so fast?

377
00:23:39,961 --> 00:23:41,087
No way.

378
00:23:42,421 --> 00:23:43,381
You have real talent.

379
00:23:45,174 --> 00:23:46,509
No.

380
00:23:46,592 --> 00:23:47,677
It can't be!

381
00:23:47,760 --> 00:23:50,638
It's beating like that thinking of him
as a character in a novel.

382
00:23:52,140 --> 00:23:53,182
That's all.

383
00:23:57,228 --> 00:24:01,065
CHAPTER 7:
WE WERE FRIENDS

384
00:24:01,149 --> 00:24:03,609
CHARACTERS
KOREAN LITERATURE: DEPENDENT PERSONALITY

385
00:24:03,693 --> 00:24:06,195
PE: LOYAL AND DEPENDABLE TYPE

386
00:24:14,787 --> 00:24:17,832
But there's no obstacle
standing in their way.

387
00:24:18,749 --> 00:24:21,878
Do I need a third guy?

388
00:24:21,961 --> 00:24:24,463
PE, KANG TAE-HA
KOREAN LITERATURE, CHOI YOON

389
00:24:24,547 --> 00:24:27,049
Han Jae-min, who studied abroad,
as the third wheel?

390
00:24:28,009 --> 00:24:29,010
No.

391
00:24:29,093 --> 00:24:30,678
He's too lightweight.

392
00:24:34,432 --> 00:24:37,143
He can be a bit prickly at times.

393
00:24:37,226 --> 00:24:39,270
Sometimes he can be childish and immature,

394
00:24:39,896 --> 00:24:42,231
but he's not a bad guy at heart.

395
00:24:42,315 --> 00:24:43,858
If any footage of this turns up online,

396
00:24:43,941 --> 00:24:46,777
I'll make you regret it.

397
00:24:49,989 --> 00:24:51,073
A regretful top?

398
00:24:54,118 --> 00:24:57,455
The kind that acts like an asshole
and later regrets it?

399
00:24:57,538 --> 00:24:58,372
That's him to a tee.

400
00:24:59,165 --> 00:25:01,459
The asshole of a math genius

401
00:25:01,542 --> 00:25:05,504
turned down offers of professorship
from every Ivy League school.

402
00:25:06,297 --> 00:25:07,798
Why would he do that?

403
00:25:08,382 --> 00:25:11,010
To go to college with his buddy
who majored in Korean literature?

404
00:25:11,093 --> 00:25:13,512
He treated him badly
but secretly liked him?

405
00:25:14,972 --> 00:25:16,224
So, is this how it goes?

406
00:25:16,807 --> 00:25:20,519
The Korean teacher had a crush on the math
teacher ever since they were little.

407
00:25:20,603 --> 00:25:22,897
Attracted by his bad boy charm.

408
00:25:22,980 --> 00:25:25,608
Seeing that,
the PE teacher had his heart broken.

409
00:25:26,359 --> 00:25:29,820
Math, never realizing how much he cared
for Korean, treated him terribly,

410
00:25:29,904 --> 00:25:32,573
and didn't realize his true feelings
until it was too late.

411
00:25:32,657 --> 00:25:36,619
Not wanting to admit it,
he deliberately avoids Korean…

412
00:25:36,702 --> 00:25:40,248
But then PE comes back
as an obsessive top.

413
00:25:40,331 --> 00:25:44,794
Regretful Math clings to Korean,
trying to win him back! Cue tears!

414
00:25:48,464 --> 00:25:49,590
Amazing!

415
00:25:49,674 --> 00:25:51,467
This dynamic is amazing.

416
00:25:51,550 --> 00:25:52,426
This ship…

417
00:25:54,303 --> 00:25:55,513
will sail.

418
00:25:57,139 --> 00:25:59,141
WE WERE FRIENDS
EPISODE 1

419
00:25:59,225 --> 00:26:00,476
IMUK

420
00:26:00,559 --> 00:26:04,522
AS DAWN BEGAN TO BREAK…

421
00:26:05,690 --> 00:26:08,693
AS USUAL, CHOI YOON WAS THE FIRST TO WAKE

422
00:26:09,777 --> 00:26:11,904
SEEING YOON SOBBING,
TAE-HA CAN'T HOLD BACK

423
00:26:11,988 --> 00:26:12,989
Are you dumb?

424
00:26:13,614 --> 00:26:14,907
Huh?

425
00:26:17,576 --> 00:26:20,288
What's so great about that asshole
who always treats you badly?

426
00:26:21,747 --> 00:26:23,874
He can be a bit prickly at times.

427
00:26:24,750 --> 00:26:26,794
Sometimes he can be childish and immature,

428
00:26:26,877 --> 00:26:28,462
but he's not a bad guy at heart.

429
00:26:29,839 --> 00:26:32,717
He's not doing it deliberately,
so don't get the wrong idea.

430
00:26:34,760 --> 00:26:36,304
HE'S JUST USING YOU

431
00:26:38,347 --> 00:26:40,099
He's just using you.

432
00:26:41,183 --> 00:26:43,561
He knows you're kind,
so he just does whatever he wants.

433
00:26:47,064 --> 00:26:48,190
I don't care.

434
00:26:50,234 --> 00:26:53,321
Still, you're the only one
who worries about me.

435
00:26:54,447 --> 00:26:56,324
You're a great friend, Tae-ha.

436
00:26:58,284 --> 00:26:59,285
Friend?

437
00:27:00,119 --> 00:27:02,538
Yeah, my best friend.

438
00:27:02,621 --> 00:27:04,081
YOON'S EYES CRINKLE AS HE SMILES

439
00:27:04,165 --> 00:27:05,583
That made me mad.

440
00:27:05,666 --> 00:27:07,126
Like you were telling me

441
00:27:07,209 --> 00:27:09,378
to keep my distance.

442
00:27:18,971 --> 00:27:19,930
TAE-HA PUSHES YOON AWAY

443
00:27:20,014 --> 00:27:21,140
What about Ju Si-on?

444
00:27:22,683 --> 00:27:23,601
What is he to you?

445
00:27:23,684 --> 00:27:26,354
TAE-HA'S VOICE TREMBLED
WITH JEALOUSY AND FEAR

446
00:27:26,437 --> 00:27:27,563
Si-on…

447
00:27:27,646 --> 00:27:28,564
CHOI YOON HESITATED

448
00:27:36,322 --> 00:27:37,156
What the heck?

449
00:27:37,823 --> 00:27:39,116
Why is this going so well?

450
00:27:41,035 --> 00:27:43,079
I shouldn't be doing this.
They're my teachers.

451
00:27:44,455 --> 00:27:45,289
No.

452
00:27:45,915 --> 00:27:47,083
No!

453
00:27:47,166 --> 00:27:50,503
It's a novel. Besides, I changed all
their names so maybe no one will realize?

454
00:27:52,713 --> 00:27:56,175
I've never written so seamlessly.
The characters, the dialogue…

455
00:27:59,345 --> 00:28:01,180
Still, this is wrong.

456
00:28:01,972 --> 00:28:04,225
What if someone finds out?

457
00:28:04,308 --> 00:28:08,020
SUBMIT A NEW PROJECT

458
00:28:17,571 --> 00:28:19,073
SUBMIT A NEW PROJECT

459
00:28:29,166 --> 00:28:30,960
But my writing is so good.

460
00:28:32,461 --> 00:28:34,755
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 1

461
00:28:36,257 --> 00:28:37,716
SAVE DRAFT

462
00:28:37,800 --> 00:28:38,843
Hey, Yoon!

463
00:28:55,484 --> 00:28:56,569
What are you doing here?

464
00:28:57,611 --> 00:28:59,905
I thought you wanted
to take Discrete Math together.

465
00:29:00,656 --> 00:29:02,116
Yeah, let's go.

466
00:29:14,253 --> 00:29:15,337
Stay away!

467
00:29:42,031 --> 00:29:44,408
BEYOND EUI-JU'S IMAGINATION
TAE-HA, YOON AND THEN…

468
00:29:54,502 --> 00:29:55,544
Okay, let's go!

469
00:29:59,590 --> 00:30:01,175
What's going on?

470
00:30:01,258 --> 00:30:03,511
AND HAN JAE-MIN

471
00:31:01,860 --> 00:31:03,862
Subtitle: Paul Carver

